#   DIFF-003: file-scoped `diff:` shows the whole file, changes highlighted

A hunk nav-URI like `diff:ast/BAST.c#L362` (the `U` link bro emits on each diff
hunk) currently opens a FILE-SCOPED `diff:` that shows only that file's changed
hunks, scrolled to the line.  For a single file the user wants the opposite of
the dir/tree view: render the WHOLE file content with the changed lines
highlighted in place (like `git diff --color` over the full file, a review
pane), so a change reads in full surrounding context.  Tree/dir `diff:` keeps
showing only changed hunks.  Method: [Issues].

##  Input

### Context
 -  `diff:` is URI-driven (`graf/DIFFREF.c`: "file or whole tree, ref vs wt or
    ref vs ref").  A file path scopes to that file; today it emits only the
    file's changed hunks.
 -  bro emits a `U` nav-URI per hunk carrying a `#L<n>` line anchor (`dog/HUNK.c`
    fragment grammar; built via `HUNKu8sMakeURI`, `graf/WEAVE.c`).  Clicking it
    re-dispatches `diff:<path>#L<n>` — the entry point for this view.
 -  Distinct from dir/tree `diff:` (changed-hunks-only), which must NOT change.

### Goals
 -  `be diff:<file>#L<n>` (file-scoped) renders the FULL file, every line, with
    added/removed/changed lines highlighted in place and the `#L<n>` anchor
    honored for scroll/jump.
 -  Tree/dir-scoped `diff:` (no single-file path) stays changed-hunks-only.
 -  Works in Plain/Color/TLV; composes the same under sub recursion.

### Constraints
 -  Producer/renderer split: graf decides the EMIT scope (full-file lines vs
    changed-hunks-only) keyed off file-vs-tree URI scope; bro owns the change
    highlighting/presentation — producers must not decide presentation.
 -  No new diff engine — reuse graf's existing file diff (`graf/DIFFREF.c`,
    `graf/WEAVE.c`); emit unchanged context lines tagged so bro highlights.
 -  `abc/` untouched; read-only `dog/HUNK` stream; all four URI slots compose.

##  WIP

### Design decisions (open — confirm in a design pass before forking)
 -  Where full-file scope is decided: a file-scoped `diff:` URI should make
    DIFFREF emit all file lines (change-tagged), not just hunks — confirm the
    branch/flag, and whether the ref-vs-ref line cap must lift for one file.
 -  Highlight encoding: which `dog/HUNK` tok tags bro already has for add/del/
    change lines, and whether full-file context needs an "unchanged" tag.

### TODOs
-[ ] Design pass: confirm the DIFFREF file-scope branch + bro's tok tagging.
-[ ] Implement full-file emit for a file-scoped `diff:`; keep tree/dir scope
      changed-hunks-only.
-[ ] Honor the `#L<n>` anchor for jump/scroll in the full-file view.
-[ ] Tests: file-scoped `diff:<file>#L<n>` output contains an UNCHANGED line
      far from any change AND the highlighted changed line, in Plain/Color/TLV;
      tree-scope `diff:` still hunks-only (regression).

### Blockers and bummers
 -  Whole-file emit on a huge file ⇒ large output; the per-file line cap may
    need a file-scope override (verify the BNOROOM-class limits).

##  Outcome
 -  Landed `eaa75793`: file-scope `diff:` reuses the `cat:` emitter
    `WEAVEEmitFull` (change-tagged, no windowing) via a `b8 full` flag threaded
    through `GRAFDiff2Layer`; tree-scope keeps windowed `WEAVEEmitDiff`.
 -  `WEAVEEmitFull` gained a `scheme` param so `dog/HUNK` routes the full-file
    hunk to the unified +/- formatter (`cat:` passes empty → byte-identical).
    Test `test/diff/11-file-scope-full`; 373/373 green.

